headline: Wall Street’s Momentum Train Hits Full Speed Into September
summary: Markets barely flinched this week — despite fresh political pressure on the Federal Reserve and tepid Nvidia Corp. revenue guidance — until a tech-led pullback Friday, amid thin trading.  Risk appetite continues to spill into nearly every corner of markets, from corporate bonds and cryptocurrencies to cyclical currencies.  The rationale feels deceptively simple: the Fed looks poised to cut interest rates, the US consumer has so far proved the doubters wrong, and the artificial intelligence story still commands momentum.
